. In this paper, we present a novel approach to the problem of deep neural networks in a hybrid context. We propose a method to train deep neural networks on a set of adversarial examples, and then to evaluate the performance of the trainees on a set of adversarial examples. The proposed method is based on the combination of a deep learning algorithm and a neural network. We demonstrate the performance of the proposed method on a set of adversarial examples. We also present a numerical example of the proposed method.
